7. Operations Plan
7.1 Development Methodology
Agile/Scrum: 2-week sprints

Test-Driven Development: 95%+ test coverage requirement

Continuous Integration: Automated testing on every commit

Weekly Releases: Feature updates every Thursday

7.2 Technology Infrastructure
Frontend: TypeScript, React, SCSS

Backend: Node.js, TypeScript, PostgreSQL

Cloud: AWS (EC2, RDS, S3, CloudFront)

Testing: Playwright for E2E, Jest for unit tests

Monitoring: Datadog, Sentry, LogRocket

7.3 Security & Compliance
Quarterly Security Audits: External penetration testing

Compliance: GDPR, CCPA, PCI DSS Level 1

Data Protection: Encryption at rest and in transit

Backup Strategy: Daily automated backups, 30-day retention

7.4 Customer Support
Tier 1: AI chatbot + knowledge base (24/7)

Tier 2: Email support (8am-8pm EST)

Tier 3: Phone support for Business/Enterprise (9am-5pm EST)

Target Metrics: < 2 hour response time, > 90% satisfaction

8. Technology Stack (Current Implementation)
8.1 Core Stack
text
Frontend:       TypeScript, HTML5, SCSS, React (Phase 2+)
Backend:        Node.js, TypeScript, Express, PostgreSQL
Testing:        Playwright, Jest, Testing Library
DevOps:         GitHub Actions, Docker, AWS
Analytics:      Google Analytics, Mixpanel, Hotjar
Payments:       Stripe, PayPal
Communication:  SendGrid, Twilio, Socket.io
8.2 Development Principles
Accessibility First: WCAG 2.1 AA compliance required for all features

Internationalization: All strings externalized, RTL support

Security by Design: Zero-trust architecture from day one

Test Automation: Comprehensive test suite covering all critical paths

Documentation: Code-level documentation required for all PRs

8.3 Scalability Architecture
Initial: Monolithic architecture for speed

Scale: Microservices when reaching 100k+ users

Database: PostgreSQL with read replicas

Caching: Redis for frequently accessed data

CDN: CloudFront for global static assets

9. Development Roadmap (20-Week Plan)
Phase 1: Foundation (Weeks 1-8) - $0 Investment
Week 1-2: Static pages, responsive design, accessibility foundation

Week 3-4: Interactive components, form validation, i18n setup

Week 5-6: Calendar system, timezone management, local storage

Week 7-8: User authentication, basic booking flow, email notifications

Deliverable: Working MVP with 3 core user flows

Phase 2: Monetization (Weeks 9-16) - $50k Seed
Week 9-12: Payment integration (Stripe), subscription management

Week 13-16: Review system, provider dashboard, advanced booking

Deliverable: Revenue-ready platform with payment processing

Phase 3: Growth (Weeks 17-24) - $250k Seed Extension
Week 17-20: Video integration, file sharing, mobile optimization

Week 21-24: Analytics dashboard, API development, partner integrations

Deliverable: Feature-complete platform ready for scaling

Phase 4: Scale (Weeks 25-32) - $1M Series A
Week 25-28: Mobile apps (iOS/Android), team features

Week 29-32: AI matching, marketplace, enterprise features

Deliverable: Multi-platform solution for global market

